# MCP environment surface — currently EMPTY by design.
#
# The servers in .mcp.json (vercel, supabase-rasifiters) are OAuth-based remote
# HTTP MCP servers. They need NO API keys here — on first use Claude Code runs a
# one-time browser login per server (see CLAUDE.md "MCP Servers").
#
# This file exists so that if a future MCP server needs a secret, it has a
# documented home:
#   1. Reference it in .mcp.json as ${SOME_KEY}
#   2. Add `SOME_KEY=` here (committed, value blank)
#   3. Copy this file to .env.mcp (gitignored) and fill the real value.
#
# EXCEPTION — render (RENDER_API_KEY):
#   Render's OAuth server does not support dynamic client registration, so the
#   browser OAuth flow fails ("Incompatible auth server: does not support
#   dynamic client registration"). Instead, render uses header auth: .mcp.json
#   passes `Authorization: Bearer ${RENDER_API_KEY}`. The key value lives in
#   .claude/settings.local.json (gitignored) under `env.RENDER_API_KEY`, which
#   Claude Code loads into the environment before it expands .mcp.json. Create
#   the key at https://dashboard.render.com/ (Account Settings → API Keys).
#   Machine-local — never commit the real value.
